title: For Sale:  Savage FCP-10 Police Model
postcontent:
This is a highly tuned and amazing accurate Savage which I truly love, unfortunately things like a divorce will make you pick between food and your favorite inanimate object.  This is my baby...You won't find a scratch or blemish, it has only been fired toughly 8 times and I am the kind of guy who can shoot 20 bullets all day and be happy as hell.  This rifle will do quarter MOA at a 100 and usually a bit better.  I am a bench rest guy and spent hours an hours perfecting the load this rifle just loves and will give you the recipe plus a few hundred rounds of its favorite snack.  
The rifle has a fluted barrel, muzzle break, accutrigger, accustock, and had the internals  coated with a heat treatment of Frog lube (cause that stuff is amazing!!) You have to see and hold this behemoth....to bad savage phased them out for a cheaper version for local police departments....this thing is getting to be scarce since they aren't going to made anytime soon and there is a demand from experienced long range shooters and decorated police trigger pullers alike because of the accuracy and weight...the heft makes it a great bench rest rifle and you can run hot loads and it wont move a millimeter off of target. 
I have topped this beast with a Bushnell Elite 6500 4.5-30 x 50 Matte Fine Multi-X Reticle with Rainguard Riflescope which I dropped $870.00 on. The rifle was 1k and there is the ammo, and if you reload I have over $2,000 worth of bullets (bullets only sold all powder and brass) if your interested. There is also a Harris SBRM 6 - 9 inch bipod with S-lock as well as a Caldwell "The Rock" Deluxe Shooting Rest - 383-774 includes the backrest and I will add the Caldwell Deluxe Universal Rear Bag 
So down to brass tacks....The original investment for everything except the bullets is just under $3,100 for this entire package.  
Good offers will not be turned away, but with over $300.00 in match grade ammo free don't waste my time.  This will not last....I actually have a meeting tomorrow morning at 8:00 am but the price isn't there,,,,,and he isn't getting all the extras....so you get close to  $2,500 and its yours and I will throw in $200.00 in match grade bullets.....man this is harder than I imagined......hell maybe i'll keep the damn thing...jk ( maybe)

title: For Sale:  Factory side fold Mini 14 extras ultimak
postcontent:
This is a very Nice Mini 14 with the original Ruger side folding stock. The rifle has one small gouge on the stock that is not very deep, just enough to remove finish. The bluing is worn on the moving parts, like the bolt contact surfaces etc. but otherwise is in great shape.

Included, and installed is the Ultimak scout mount, and a set of Tech sights. The Ultimak has been used with an Aimpoint micro dot, and was an excellent combination. As far as iron sights go the Mini 14s are always lacking but the new Tech sight rear sight makes a world of difference. I do not like peep sights, but I have no issue using the Mini with the new rear sight. There is also a M14 style flash hider installed to give it that A-team feel. The original parts, sights, and heat shield are included.

According to Ruger the Ser# puts it at a MFG date in 1985, and with a 1:10 twist barrel. Mini 14s are chambered in 5.56, and I have fired 62g green tip ammunition with great results, and no key holing.

I am including several magazines with, all but one function. That one is rusty and bet up. It works great to practice reloads, or open beers. the others are thermold, one is a new Tapco magazine that was used once, and the short magazine is a 20rd. None to my knowledge are factory magazines.
